    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) is mitigated by the robust quantitative validation metric (E/uval <1.96 for all QoIs across all 11 specimens) and the conservative acceptance bounds (<10% relative error). The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending.",
